@startuml
title Cloud Food Corner - Current Application Flow

actor Customer
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "HomeController" as HomeController
participant "MenuController" as MenuController
participant "OrderController" as OrderController
participant "MenuService" as MenuService
participant "MenuItemRepository" as MenuItemRepository
participant "OrderRepository" as OrderRepository
database "H2 Database" as DB
entity "Category.CategoryType" as CategoryType
entity "Order Entity" as Order
participant "Thymeleaf home.html" as HomeView
participant "Thymeleaf menu.html" as MenuView
participant "Thymeleaf orderForm.html" as OrderFormView

== Home Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open application
Browser -> HomeController : GET /
HomeController -> HomeView : return "home"
HomeView --> Browser : Render homepage
Browser --> Customer : Show home page

== Menu Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open menu
Browser -> MenuController : GET /menu

MenuController -> MenuService : getAllItems()
MenuService -> MenuItemRepository : findAll()
MenuItemRepository -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuItemRepository : menu items
MenuItemRepository --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService --> MenuController : menuItems

MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(MAIN_COURSE)
MenuService -> MenuItemRepository : findAll()
MenuItemRepository -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuItemRepository : menu items
MenuItemRepository --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService -> CategoryType : filter by MAIN_COURSE
MenuService --> MenuController : mainCourse

MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(STREET_FOOD)
MenuService -> MenuItemRepository : findAll()
MenuItemRepository -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuItemRepository : menu items
MenuItemRepository --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService -> CategoryType : filter by STREET_FOOD
MenuService --> MenuController : streetFood

MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(SWEETS)
MenuService -> MenuItemRepository : findAll()
MenuItemRepository -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuItemRepository : menu items
MenuItemRepository --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService -> CategoryType : filter by SWEETS
MenuService --> MenuController : sweets

MenuController -> MenuService : getByCategory(BEVERAGES)
MenuService -> MenuItemRepository : findAll()
MenuItemRepository -> DB : load menu items
DB --> MenuItemRepository : menu items
MenuItemRepository --> MenuService : menuItems
MenuService -> CategoryType : filter by BEVERAGES
MenuService --> MenuController : beverages

MenuController -> CategoryType : read values()

note right of MenuController
Adds model attributes:
- menuItems
- mainCourse
- streetFood
- sweets
- beverages
- categories
end note

MenuController -> MenuView : return "menu" with model
MenuView --> Browser : Render categorized menu
Browser --> Customer : Show menu page

== Order Form ==
Customer -> Browser : Click "Place Order"
Browser -> OrderController : GET /order/current
OrderController -> Order : new Order()
OrderController -> OrderFormView : return "orderForm" with order
OrderFormView --> Browser : Render order form
Browser --> Customer : Show order form

== Order Submission ==
Customer -> Browser : Submit order details
Browser -> OrderController : POST /order
OrderController -> OrderController : validate submitted Order

alt Validation errors
    OrderController -> OrderFormView : return "orderForm"
    OrderFormView --> Browser : Render validation errors
    Browser --> Customer : Show form with field errors
else Valid order
    OrderController -> OrderRepository : save(order)
    OrderRepository -> DB : insert into orders
    DB --> OrderRepository : saved order
    OrderRepository --> OrderController : saved order
    OrderController -> OrderController : log submitted Order
    OrderController --> Browser : redirect:/
    Browser -> HomeController : GET /
    HomeController -> HomeView : return "home"
    HomeView --> Browser : Render homepage
    Browser --> Customer : Show redirected home page
end

note over Browser, DB
Current state:
- Server-rendered Spring MVC app
- Thymeleaf templates for UI
- H2 in-memory database configured
- Menu items are loaded through MenuItemRepository
- MenuService still filters categories in memory after loading all items
- Order form binds to the Order entity
- Valid submitted orders are saved through OrderRepository
- No cart, checkout, payment gateway, or order tracking flow yet
end note

== Future Improvements ==
participant "CartController" as CartController
participant "CheckoutController" as CheckoutController
participant "PaymentController" as PaymentController
participant "Payment Gateway" as PaymentGateway

Browser -> CartController : POST /cart
CartController -> DB : store cart state
DB --> CartController : updated cart
CartController --> Browser : updated cart view/response

Browser -> CheckoutController : POST /checkout
CheckoutController -> OrderRepository : save finalized order
OrderRepository -> DB : persist order and status
DB --> OrderRepository : order id / status
OrderRepository --> CheckoutController : saved order
CheckoutController -> PaymentController : initiate payment
PaymentController -> PaymentGateway : process payment
PaymentGateway --> PaymentController : payment status
PaymentController --> CheckoutController : payment result
CheckoutController --> Browser : order confirmation

note over CartController, PaymentGateway
Recommended next steps:
- Use repository queries for category-specific menu loading
- Add cart persistence and cart UI state
- Add checkout flow before final order submission
- Integrate payment processing
- Add order confirmation and status tracking
- Persist selected menu items with the order
end note
@enduml
